description:
Trouble with Lichen

written by John Wyndham
read by Joanna Tope
first broadcast, 2007

In another John Wyndham classic, Biochemist Diana Brackley and her boss Francis Saxover have discovered that a rare strain of lichen can slow the ageing process. Idealistic Diana embarks on a lifelong mission to ensure that their discovery will benefit man-, and more particularly, woman-kind. But the trouble with lichen is that there&#039;s not enough for everyone... Joanna Tope reads this new to BBC 7 commission in five parts, directed by Eilidh McCreadie
